      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIO BON BON (3) unwanted in betting but showed good early dash and led until late, finishing second and beaten a neck (25.18) at Sale in a Bottom Up - Grade 7 over 435m. Can measure up this time. TAKE A PANTHER (1) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 2 lengths (17.29) behind Mccreery at Healesville. Bold showing expected. NATINA (2) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Dr. Quibble (20.39) in a Rank Limit - Restricted Win. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to her credit. Expected to be in the finish again. GOTHAM PIXIE (8) is worth including.",
